BW is rather impacted by parity: higher parities are associated with higher BW

Increasing maternal age is significantly associated with an increase of SB risk (pvalue: 0.00012), but this increase is very small. Maternal age category is also associated with changes in SB risk: being in age categories (10, 20), (20,25) or (35,40), (40,70) increases the risk of having a stillborn. The risk is the greatest for mothers aged (30-70).

Parity does not seem to impact stillbirth risk.
